          "CRITIQUE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Authors \"selected the 181Ta(G,N)180Ta reaction,",
                " because several experimental data exist on the",
                " cross-section of this reaction up to a photon energy",
                " of 35 MeV but do not mention what one exactly (data",
                " from different experiments noticeably disagree to",
                " each other, as is presented in Fig. 5 of article)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The yields of photonuclear reactions were determined",
                " using the activation formula (1) of the article.",
                "The cross sections averaged over the bremsstrahlung",
                " flux from the threshold Eth of the reaction under",
                " study to the end-point energy of the bremsstrahlung",
                " spectrum Eg-max were obtained using activation",
                " formula by replacing the integral number of photons",
                " incident on the sample to the integral number of",
                " photons in the energy range (Ethresold - Eg-max)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainty of the values of all",
                " flux-averaged cross-sections is equated to the",
                " uncertainty of the values of relative yields.",
                "The measurement uncertainties of experimental values",
                " of reaction yield ratios was determined as the",
                " squared sum of the standard deviation of the",
                " arithmetic mean of the relative yield values and",
                " systematical errors (are described in Paragraph C",
                " of article)"
              ]
            }
          ],
